In this implementation, we use two stacks to simulate the behavior of a queue. The `enqueue` method adds an item to the end of the queue by appending it to the `stack1`. The `dequeue` method removes and returns the item from the front of the queue. If the `stack2` is empty, we transfer items from `stack1` to `stack2` until the front item is at the top of `stack2`, ensuring that the next item to be dequeued is at the top of the `stack2`.
